# Recognized automatically by Netlify and Cloudflare Pages (ignored, harmless,
# on any other host). Forces every request to revalidate with the server
# before using a cached copy, instead of trusting a cached copy indefinitely —
# the same problem class documented in CLAUDE.md's caching gotcha, fixed at
# the hosting layer as a second line of defense alongside the ?v=N convention
# in index.html (which still matters for hosts that don't read this file,
# e.g. GitHub Pages, and for local dev).
/*
  Cache-Control: no-cache
